    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, I'm seeing a 500 Internal Server Error on our /api/v1/checkout/process endpoint. It only happens intermittently when we hit high concurrency, but it's not consistently tied to a specific payload. Here are the last few lines from the error log:\n\n[2023-10-27 14:22:01] ERROR: ConnectionPoolTimeout during checkout sequence\n[2023-10-27 14:22:03] ERROR: Failed to acquire connection from pool: pool exhausted\n[2023-10-27 14:22:05] CRITICAL: Unexpected termination of worker process 8829\n[2023-10-27 14:22:05] ERROR: Connection reset by peer\n\nIt seems like something is starving the connection pool or dropping the worker, but I can't find a memory leak. Any idea what might be causing this sudden instability under load?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
